ifier>\n                    <msContents>\n                        <textLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin</textLang>\n                    </msContents>\n                    <physDesc>\n                        <objectDesc>\n                            <supportDesc>\n                                <support><p>Two rejoined fragments of a large plaque of a grey-white marble with blue veining. The surface is dark due to exposue and surface accretions, and presents a grey-brown appearance. The stone is broken on all sides in an irregular shape. The reverse is smooth. The measurements recorded in NSA are notably under the reality.</p>\n                                    <material ana=\"#material.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble</material>\n                                    <objectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html\">plaque</objectType>\n                                    <dimensions>\n                                        <height unit=\"cm\">28.8</height>\n                                        <width unit=\"cm\">33.1</width>\n                                        <depth unit=\"cm\">3.3-2.8 (top to bottom)</depth>\n                                    </dimensions>\n                                </support>\n                                <condition ana=\"#condition.fragments.contiguous\"/>\n\t\t    </supportDesc>\n                            <layoutDesc>\n                                <layout><p>Remains of two lines of monumental letters; the gap below line 2 is greater (up to 7.5 cm) than the gap between lines 1 and 2 (5.5 cm), which could suggest that this is the last line of the text.</p>\n                                    <rs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled</rs>\n                                    <damage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t</layout>\n                            </layoutDesc>\n                        </objectDesc>\n                        <handDesc>\n                            <handNote><p>Large and very precisely cut letters with neat serifs, with a wide v-cut and a wide module. Interpunct of an elegant comma form (note again that the NSA measurements are incorrect and significantly under).</p>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">80 (preserved; probably c.82 originally)</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line2\" to=\"line2\">Line 2</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">70</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">55</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                            </handNote>\n                        </handDesc>\n                    </physDesc>\n                    <history>\n                        <origin>\n                            <origPlace>\n                                <placeName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503\">Syracusae</placeName>\t\t\n                                <placeName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2523083\">Siracusa</placeName>\n                            \t<geo>37.08415, 15.27628</geo>\n\t\t</origPlace>\n                            <origDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0012\" notAfter-custom=\"0066\" evidence=\"lettering office\">Augustan or Julio-Claudian</origDate>\n                        </origin>\n                        <provenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"1964\">From excavation in 1964 of a series of cisterns in Villa Maria, specifically cistern N, flanking viale Luigi Cadorna<geo>37.074921, 15.286895</geo></provenance><!-- manually placed geo for cistern N, based upon map in NSA 1971, p.582 fig. 1-->\n                        <provenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">Prag 2015-01-15, Magazzino B, cassette 10</provenance>\n                        <acquisition/>\n                    </history>\n                </msDesc>\n            </sourceDesc>\n        </fileDesc>\n        <encodingDesc>\n             <p>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines</p>\n             <xi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 <xi:fallback>\n                     <p>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values</p>\n                 </xi:fallback>\n             </xi:include>\n\t  <xi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     <xi:fallback>\n\t       <p>ISicily glyphs authority list</p>\n\t     </xi:fallback>\n\t   </xi:include>\n         </encodingDesc>\n        <profileDesc>\n            <calendarDesc>\n                <calendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    <p>Julian Calendar</p>\n                </calendar>\n            </calendarDesc>\n            <langUsage>\n                <language ident=\"en\">English</language>\n                <language ident=\"it\">Italian</language>\n                <language ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek</language>\n                <language ident=\"la\">Latin</language>\n                <language ident=\"he\">Hebrew</language>\n                <language ident=\"phn\">Phoenician</language>\n                <language ident=\"xpu\">Punic</language>\n                <language ident=\"osc\">Oscan</language>\n                <language ident=\"xly\">Elymian</language>\n                <language ident=\"scx\">Sikel</language>\n                <language ident=\"sxc\">Sikan</language>\n            </langUsage>\n            <textClass>\n                <keywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    <term ana=\"#function.building\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/86.html\">building</term>\n                </keywords>\n            </textClass>\n        </profileDesc>\n        <revisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            <listChange>\n                <change when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages</change>\n                <change when=\"2020-10-19\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag added text div, museum info and dimensions from NSA edition</change>\n            \t\t<change when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography</change>\n\t    <change when=\"2020-12-17\" who=\"#system\">Updated Zenodo DOI</change>\n            \t<change when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references</change>\n                <change when=\"2024-06-29\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag revised from autopsy and photograph and added images</change>\n\t</listChange>\n        </revisionDesc>\n    </teiHeader>\n    <facsimile>\n        <surface type=\"front\">\n            <graphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic000621_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-15</desc>\n            </graphic>\n            <graphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic000621.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-15</desc>\n            </graphic>\n         </surface>\n        <surface type=\"rear\">\n            <graphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic000621_rear_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-15</desc>\n            </graphic>\n            <graphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic000621_rear.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-15</desc>\n            </graphic>\n        </surface>\n    </facsimile>\n    <text>\n        <body>\n            <div type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                <ab>\n                    <lb n=\"1\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>x <g ref=\"#interpunct\">·</g> tr<gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    <lb n=\"2\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> <unclear>v</unclear>etust<gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                </ab>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"apparatus\">\n                <listApp>\n                    <app><note>Text from autopsy</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"1\"><note>Wilson: X TP</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"2\"><note>Fallico, Wilson: [V]ETUST[ATE</note></app>\n                </listApp>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"translation\">\n                <p><!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div--></p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"commentary\">\n                <p>As noted already by Fallico, the surviving letters in line 2 are almost certainly part of a phrase such as 'vetustate conlapsam... restituit' ('falling down through old age, he restored...') or similar, recording therefore a work of restoration or reconstruction of an existing building. Fallico further observes (NSA 1971, p.635 n.1) that the letters X·TR in line 1 are probably part of imperial titulature, either along the lines of  [PONT·MA]X·TR[IB·POTEST] or [COS]·X·TR[IB·POTEST] or IMP]·X·TR[IB·POTEST]. Various such permutations are possible, fitting to Augustus after 12 BC, but also to Claudius (45 AD) or Nero (66 AD).</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"bibliography\">\n                <listBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    <bibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"NSA\">\n                        <author>Fallico</author>\n                        <title>NSA</title>\n                        <date>1971</date>\n                        <citedRange>634-635 fig.51</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392</ref>\n                    </bibl>\n                    <bibl>\n                        <author>Wilson</author>\n                        <date>1990</date>\n                        <citedRange>40 n.70</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/VF9MMBI9\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509</ref>\n                    </bibl>\n                </listBibl>\n\t   <listBibl type=\"discussion\"><bibl/></listBibl>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>\n",
